On Wed, 15 Oct 2003 JWAzevedo(-at-)aol.com wrote:

> About those Mexican engines: I had one shop encourage me to get one and
another shop pooh-pooh'ed them, saying, with a kind of a sniff, "Well,
that's fine if you want a low-compression engine."  Any other thoughts
from those who've tried them?

Well, they are low-compression.  They run fine on any gas I've fed them
and _never_ ping.  That, to me, is a plus.

There might be a tiny performance loss, but the reliability is worth it.

